TY  - JOUR
AU  - Hatfield, John William
AU  - Kominers, Scott Duke
AU  - Westkamp, Alexander
T1  - Stability, Strategy-Proofness, and Cumulative Offer Mechanisms
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdaa052
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 88
IS  - 3
SP  - 1457
EP  - 1502
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We characterize when a stable and strategy-proof mechanism is guaranteed to exist in the setting of many-to-one matching with contracts. We introduce three novel conditions—observable substitutability, observable size monotonicity, and non-manipulability via contractual terms—and show that when these conditions are satisfied, the cumulative offer mechanism is the unique mechanism that is stable and strategy-proof (for workers). Moreover, we show that our three conditions are, in a sense, necessary: if the choice function of some firm fails any of our three conditions, we can construct unit-demand choice functions for the other firms such that no stable and strategy-proof mechanism exists. Thus, our results provide a rationale for the ubiquity of cumulative offer mechanisms in practice.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdaa052
ER  - 



