TY  - JOUR
AU  - Haghpanah, Nima
AU  - Hartline, Jason
T1  - When Is Pure Bundling Optimal?
PY  - 2021
Y1  - 2021/05/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdaa053
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 88
IS  - 3
SP  - 1127
EP  - 1156
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We study when pure bundling, i.e., offering only the grand bundle of all products, is optimal for a multi-product monopolist. Pure bundling is optimal if consumers with higher values for the grand bundle have higher relative values for smaller bundles compared to the grand bundle. Conversely, pure bundling is not optimal if consumers with higher values for the grand bundle have lower relative values. We prove the results by decomposing the problem into simpler ones in which types can be ranked according to their values for the grand bundle.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdaa053
ER  - 



